Sentencas: Double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+delta (YBSCC) is synthesized by the EDTA citrate complexing method, and investigated as a novel cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: There are no serious reactions between YBSCC and La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) except a slight peak shift.
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of the YBSCC sample occurs a semiconductor metal transition at about 350 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of the YBSCC sample is 16.4 x 10(-6) K-1 between 30 degrees C and 850 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance of 0.036 Omega cm(2) is achieved at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of a single cell with the YBSCC cathode on a 300 mu m-thick LSGM electrolyte are 398 mW cm(-2) and 272 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study suggests that the double-perovskite YBSCC can be potential candidate for utilization as IT-SOFCs cathode.
Titulo: Performance of double-perovskite YBa0.5Sr0.5Co1.4Cu0.6O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
